[49m[38;5;9m- 131     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled with data events on the assignment and review-queue tables; data events on the audit-archive S3 buckets. Review-queue API invocations logged at the API Gateway and Lambda layers. CloudTrail logs encrypted with KMS and retained per the institution's records-retention policy (typically several years for credentialing records, longer for compliance attestations).  |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled with data events on the assignment and review-queue tables; data events on the audit-archive S3 buckets. Review-queue API invocations logged at the API Gateway and Lambda layers. CloudTrail logs encrypted with KMS and retained per the institution's records-retention policy (typically several years for credentialing records, longer for compliance attestations). Forward CloudTrail data events to a dedicated audit AWS account isolated from the production data plane so that production-role compromises cannot tamper with the audit trail.  |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Retention and Immutability** | The architectural retention floor for matching artifacts (assignment records, drift events, review decisions, audit-archive objects) is the longest of: (a) the HIPAA 6-year minimum, (b) the institution's documented credentialing-record retention policy, (c) the state-specific credentialing retention statute, and (d) the network-adequacy attestation retention requirement. Many institutions land at 7 to 10 years. Apply S3 Object Lock in Compliance mode on the audit-archive bucket for immutability (once written, objects cannot be deleted or overwritten until the retention period expires). Apply an S3 lifecycle policy that transitions objects to S3 Glacier Deep Archive after 90 days (active queries use the Glue-cataloged Athena layer; the raw objects are rarely accessed directly after the first week). |
