[49m[38;5;9m- 27    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Amazon QuickSight for the operational and compliance dashboards.** Network adequacy by specialty and geography, provider-directory accuracy metrics (percent of providers with verified-within-90-days NPI assignments, percent with current addresses, percent with current taxonomies), drift event rates, review-queue depth, and cohort-stratified accuracy. QuickSight on Athena over the Glue-cataloged data, with row-level security where institutional policy requires it.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon QuickSight for the operational and compliance dashboards.** Network adequacy by specialty and geography, provider-directory accuracy metrics (percent of providers with verified-within-90-days NPI assignments, percent with current addresses, percent with current taxonomies), drift event rates, review-queue depth, and cohort-stratified accuracy. QuickSight on Athena over the Glue-cataloged data, with row-level security where institutional policy requires it.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **AWS Lake Formation for column-level and row-level access controls on the audit archive.** The Glue-cataloged audit tables contain PHI-adjacent data (license numbers, personal addresses, match-decision context). QuickSight has named row-level security, but a direct Athena query against the same catalog has no row-level enforcement unless Lake Formation governs the access. Register the audit-archive tables in Lake Formation. Apply column-level permissions to restrict license-number and personal-address columns to the credentialing-leadership and compliance-officer principals. Apply row-level security filters (tag-based access control on the `provider_segment` column) so that operations staff for Medicare Advantage cannot query Medicaid-segment records and vice versa. Define three principal groups: credentialing-leadership (full access), compliance-audit (full access, read-only), and operations-analytics (aggregate metrics only, no row-level PHI-adjacent fields). This prevents the common failure where a QuickSight dataset author exposes more data via a shared dashboard or an ad-hoc Athena session than the access policy intends.
