[49m[38;5;9m- 15    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Amazon OpenSearch Service for the registry candidate-generation index.** The NPPES file has millions of records; for real-time individual lookup during onboarding, you need an indexed substrate that supports the equivalents of the blocking passes (license-number-plus-state lookup, name-plus-state-plus-taxonomy lookup, address-zip-plus-name lookup). OpenSearch with custom analyzers (lowercase, ASCII-folding, phonetic encoding for names, exact-match for NPI and license numbers) is a good fit. Refresh the index from each monthly NPPES download. For real-time lookups, query OpenSearch directly. For batch refreshes, you can run the comparison entirely in Glue/Spark over the parquet-converted NPPES file, but having OpenSearch available for individual lookups simplifies the credentialing onboarding workflow.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon OpenSearch Service for the registry candidate-generation index.** The NPPES file has millions of records; for real-time individual lookup during onboarding, you need an indexed substrate that supports the equivalents of the blocking passes (license-number-plus-state lookup, name-plus-state-plus-taxonomy lookup, address-zip-plus-name lookup). OpenSearch with custom analyzers (lowercase, ASCII-folding, phonetic encoding for names, exact-match for NPI and license numbers) is a good fit. Refresh the index from each monthly NPPES download. For real-time lookups, query OpenSearch directly. For batch refreshes, you can run the comparison entirely in Glue/Spark over the parquet-converted NPPES file, but having OpenSearch available for individual lookups simplifies the credentialing onboarding workflow. OpenSearch availability is a single point of failure for the real-time onboarding path; the candidate-generator Lambda implements a fallback chain: (1) query OpenSearch with a 2-second timeout; (2) if OpenSearch is unavailable or latency exceeds the budget, fall back to a direct NPI Registry API query (sufficient for license-number-plus-state and name-plus-state lookups); (3) if the API path also fails or the candidate set exceeds complexity thresholds, hand off to the asynchronous scoring path via SQS with a "queued for matching" status visible in the credentialing UI. A CloudWatch alarm fires on chronic OpenSearch availability issues (three consecutive health-check failures within 5 minutes) to trigger operational intervention before the fallback path becomes the steady state.
