[49m[38;5;9m- 1041      [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Cross-recipe orchestration with patient matching (recipe 5.1).** The same DynamoDB instance and the same Glue catalog can host both the patient-matching and provider-matching artifacts. Where it makes sense, share the matching-primitives library (blocking passes, comparators, Fellegi-Sunter combiner) as a versioned Lambda layer or Glue Python library so improvements to the comparators benefit both recipes. The provider-matching pipeline is structurally simpler than the patient one, but the operational patterns (review queue, audit, drift detection, equity monitoring) are shared and worth packaging as a shared substrate.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       1041[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-recipe orchestration with patient matching (recipe 5.1).** The same DynamoDB instance and the same Glue catalog can host both the patient-matching and provider-matching artifacts. The matching-primitives library is a versioned Lambda layer (for real-time paths) and a Glue Python library (for batch paths) that hosts the shared blocking passes (metaphone generation, n-gram tokenization, ZIP5 extraction), comparators (Jaro-Winkler, Damerau-Levenshtein, token-set overlap, phonetic agreement), and the Fellegi-Sunter combiner. Each recipe pins a specific library version in its deployment configuration (e.g., `matching-primitives-v2.3`); upgrading requires an explicit version bump and re-validation against the recipe's gold set. The audit archive uses a shared-substrate cross-recipe consumption pattern: both recipe 5.1 and recipe 5.2 write to the same Glue-cataloged audit tables (partitioned by `recipe_id` and `run_date`), enabling cross-recipe analytics (e.g., "which providers also appear as patients in the patient-matching pipeline") without duplicating the Athena/QuickSight infrastructure. The version-coupling contract ensures that a comparator improvement validated in recipe 5.1's gold set does not silently degrade recipe 5.2's performance: each recipe's CI pipeline runs its own gold-set regression before accepting a library version bump.
