[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The assignment record should carry the matched Type 1 NPI as the primary anchor plus a list of current Type 2 affiliations. Each affiliation entry carries the affiliated organization name, the Type 2 NPI, an effective date range, and a primary-billing flag indicating whether the provider currently bills primarily through that entity. Drift detection should surface `type2_affiliation_added` and `type2_affiliation_removed` as separate event types from Type 1 drift, because different downstream consumers care about different changes: claims-validation subscribes to Type 2 affiliation events (because billing NPIs are Type 2), network-adequacy reporting subscribes to both (because affiliation determines which organizations the provider practices under), and the credentialing system subscribes primarily to Type 1 events (because the individual identity is what gets credentialed).
