[49m[38;5;9m- 13    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Amazon DynamoDB for the provider-NPI assignment table, the re-verification schedule, and the review queue.** Three tables, each with a clear role. `provider-npi-assignment` keyed on `internal_provider_id` holds the active NPI assignment, the drift snapshot, the match metadata, and the re-verification timestamp. `verification-schedule` keyed on `(verification_due_date, internal_provider_id)` holds the scheduled re-verification work, sortable by due date so the daily verification job can pull due-or-overdue records efficiently. `provider-review-queue` keyed on `(queue_id, candidate_pair_id)` holds candidate pairs awaiting human review, mirroring the structure from recipe 5.1. DynamoDB's single-digit-millisecond reads support real-time NPI lookups for new-provider onboarding, and on-demand capacity handles the bursty pattern of batch refresh days vs quiet days.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon DynamoDB for the provider-NPI assignment table, the re-verification schedule, and the review queue.** Three tables, each with a clear role. `provider-npi-assignment` keyed on `internal_provider_id` holds the active NPI assignment, the drift snapshot, the match metadata, and the re-verification timestamp. `verification-schedule` keyed on `internal_provider_id` (with a GSI on `verification_due_date` for the daily job's date-range query) holds the scheduled re-verification work; each provider has at most one row, preventing stale-entry accumulation across re-verification cycles. `provider-review-queue` keyed on `(queue_id, candidate_pair_id)` holds candidate pairs awaiting human review, mirroring the structure from recipe 5.1. DynamoDB's single-digit-millisecond reads support real-time NPI lookups for new-provider onboarding, and on-demand capacity handles the bursty pattern of batch refresh days vs quiet days.
